      "text": "There is a tendency to write a heading that explains what is coming next. These don't scan well when reading to find something you have read before. Better to write a one-word heading and do the explaining in a paragraph that follows. Sometimes if feels like a challenge to reduce a section to a single word especially when the section hasn't been written yet. If the heading really needs to be a better description then maybe this is your text telling you that it wants to be its own page."
